President Obama made a statement regarding a commercial agreement between Boeing and Lion Air during his visit to Bali, Indonesia. He emphasized the trade and investment opportunities in the Asia Pacific region and highlighted the potential for job creation in the United States. The deal between Lion Air, one of the fastest-growing airlines in the world, and Boeing is said to result in over 100,000 jobs in the US. This agreement represents the largest deal in Boeing's history, with over 200 planes to be sold. The US administration and the Ex-Im Bank played a crucial role in facilitating the deal. President Obama praised both Lion Air and Boeing for their success and highlighted the benefits for both the people in the region and American workers.